The College of Engineering at the Florida Institute of Technology invites nominations and applications for the position of Head of the Electrical and Computer Engineering Department, with a starting date of August 1, 2006.
Faculty in the Department offer B.S., M.S. and Ph.D. degrees in Electrical and Computer Engineering. Each of the undergraduate programs is fully accredited.
Qualified applicants are expected to have a Ph.D. degree in electrical or computer engineering, outstanding leadership and administrative 
skills, a strong record of research performance, dedication to  education, a record of professional activities and credentials 
commensurate with the appointment as a full professor in the department. Applicants should send a complete curricula vitae, a three 
page resume, a statement of the candidate's professional interests and vision, and a list of five professional references via email to 
ECEsearch@fit.edu or via fax to (321) 674-8192. Alternatively, an application package or nominations may be mailed to: ECE Department 
Head Search Committee, Florida Tech College of Engineering, 150 West University Boulevard, Melbourne, FL 32901. For more information visit 
the department's web page at http://ee.fit.edu/HeadSearch.html. The review of applications will continue until the position is filled. Florida Institute of Technology is an Equal Opportunity Employer committed to excellence through diversity.
